==English==

===Etymology===
Compound of [[under]] + [[garment]] + [[-s]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-undergarments.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''undergarments''' ''(mainly plural only)''

# [[garment]]s intended to be worn underneath other garments; [[underwear]].
# (''religion'') [[clothes]] worn under an outer layer, out of sight upon one’s person.  Usually thought to be endowed with mystical qualities. 

====Synonyms====
*[[Jesus jammies]] (2)

